# QA: COMPREHENSIVE RULE CALLING GUIDE

> **TL;DR:** This reference guide shows how to properly call all QA rules at the right time during the post-build semantic review process.

## 🔍 RULE CALLING BASICS

Remember these key principles:
1. Always use the `fetch_rules` tool to load rules
2. Use exact rule paths
3. Load components only when needed

## 📋 MAIN QA ENTRY POINT

When user types "/qa", load the main entry point:

```
fetch_rules with "shared/niko/visual-maps/van-qa-main"
```

## 📋 UTILITY COMPONENTS

Load these when needed based on review results:

```
- For reports: fetch_rules with "shared/niko/visual-maps/van-qa-utils/reports"
- For fixes: fetch_rules with "shared/niko/visual-maps/van-qa-utils/common-fixes"
- For transitions: fetch_rules with "shared/niko/visual-maps/van-qa-utils/mode-transitions"
```

## ⚠️ CRITICAL REMINDERS

Remember to call these rules at these specific points:
- ALWAYS load the main QA entry point when "/qa" is typed
- ALWAYS load reports after completing the semantic review
- ALWAYS load mode-transitions after successful review (QA gates REFLECT for L2+)
- ALWAYS load common-fixes after failed review

## 🔄 FULL REVIEW SEQUENCE

Complete sequence for a QA semantic review process:

1. Load main entry: `shared/niko/visual-maps/van-qa-main`
2. Perform semantic review (KISS/DRY/YAGNI/Completeness/Regression/Integrity/Integration Insight)
3. Apply fixes directly during review
4. If pass, load: `shared/niko/visual-maps/van-qa-utils/reports`
5. If pass, load: `shared/niko/visual-maps/van-qa-utils/mode-transitions`
6. If fail, load: `shared/niko/visual-maps/van-qa-utils/common-fixes`

**Note:** After fixing issues, user should re-run `/qa` to re-validate.
